<nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="cs-breadcrumbs"><div class="cs-breadcrumbs-container"><ol class="cs-breadcrumb-list"><li class="cs-breadcrumb-item"><a class="cs-breadcrumb-link" href="/">Home</a></li><li class="cs-breadcrumb-item"><span class="cs-breadcrumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span><a class="cs-breadcrumb-link" href="/service-areas/">Service Areas</a></li><li class="cs-breadcrumb-item"><span class="cs-breadcrumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span><span class="cs-breadcrumb-current" aria-current="page">Las Alturas</span></li></ol></div></nav><section id="services-hero-532"><picture class="cs-bg-picture"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-48.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Serving Las Alturas Since 2005</span><h1 class="cs-title">Landscaping Services in <span class="cs-color">Las Alturas, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Landscape renovation, irrigation upgrades, and hardscaping for established Las Alturas properties. Designed for mature lots, deep caliche, and Organ Mountain views.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><picture class="cs-picture"><img alt="Paver patio install on a mature landscape renovation in Las Alturas, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-pavers-3.jpeg" height="503" width="480" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Las Alturas</span><h2 class="cs-title">Refreshing Established Landscapes on the Mesa</h2><p class="cs-text">Las Alturas ("The Heights") is an established residential area east of Las Cruces, with most homes built between the 1980s and early 2000s. Lots here are larger than in newer communities, and many properties have mature trees, aging shrubs, and irrigation systems that are long past their prime.</p><p class="cs-text">That history is an asset, not a problem. Mature shade trees, settled soil, and existing hardscape give us a head start. Our job is to update what needs it (old drip lines, overgrown plantings, crumbling retaining walls) while keeping the things that already work. We know these neighborhoods well and can spot what stays, what goes, and what just needs a trim.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="areas-services-610"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What We Do Here</span><h2 class="cs-title">Services Available in Las Alturas</h2></div><div class="cs-grid"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Design</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Renovation plans that work with existing mature trees and larger lot layouts unique to Las Alturas.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-design/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscaping &amp; Install</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Overgrown plant removal, new bed installs, and grading corrections on settled Las Alturas lots.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-hardscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Hardscaping &amp; Patios</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Retaining wall repair, new patios, and walkways on the larger Las Alturas properties that have room to grow.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/hardscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Convert thirsty turf to low-water native beds while keeping the shade trees that define Las Alturas yards.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-irrigation.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Irrigation &amp; Sprinkler</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Full irrigation system replacements for Las Alturas homes with 20- to 30-year-old drip and sprinkler lines.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/irrigation/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Deep pruning for overgrown trees and shrubs, plus seasonal cleanup for large Las Alturas lots.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-maintenance/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li></ul><aside class="cs-area-info"><h3 class="cs-area-title">One Call, One Crew, All Six Services</h3><p class="cs-area-text">Older Las Alturas properties often need several things at once: replace the irrigation, prune the trees, rebuild a retaining wall, and redesign the beds. One crew handling everything means less disruption and a single guarantee.</p><ul class="cs-area-bullets"><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Design-build under one roof</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Workmanship guarantee</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Mature landscape renovation experts</li></ul></aside></div></div></section><section id="areas-landmarks-620"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Where We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Alturas Neighborhoods We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We work throughout the Las Alturas area, from the original subdivisions near Lohman Ave to the custom homes along the mesa ridge. Each pocket has different lot sizes, tree cover, and soil conditions. We plan around those details on every project.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div><picture class="cs-picture"><img alt="Flagstone patio install on a Las Alturas neighborhood landscape renovation" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-patios-2.jpeg" height="480" width="580" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-neighborhoods"><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Las Alturas Proper <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">The core of the neighborhood. Mostly 1980s and 1990s homes with mature trees, aging irrigation, and landscaping ready for a refresh.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Las Alturas Estates <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Custom-built homes on larger lots. More room for outdoor living spaces, retaining walls, and phased landscape upgrades.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">High Range <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Higher-elevation lots with panoramic Organ Mountain views. Wind-tolerant plantings and good drainage are key here.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Las Colinas <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Rolling terrain with established shade trees. Many homes here need irrigation line replacement and overgrown shrub removal.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Rincon Mesa <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Quiet streets with a mix of tract and custom homes. Deep caliche layers require extra soil prep for new plantings.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Del Rey Blvd Area <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Near retail and restaurants along Del Rey. Some commercial properties here also need low-maintenance landscape updates.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-why-353" class="cs-why-light"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper">Local Know-How</span><h2 class="cs-title">What Makes Las Alturas Landscapes Different</h2><p class="cs-intro">Las Alturas properties are 20 to 40 years old. That means mature trees, tired irrigation, and hardscape that has weathered decades of sun and monsoons. Here is how we approach renovation work in this area.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-1"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-15.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"></picture><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-2"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-53.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Deep Caliche Layer</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Las Alturas sits on thick caliche hardpan. When we add new trees or shrubs, we trench through it and amend the backfill so roots can spread without hitting a wall of calcium carbonate.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Mature Overgrowth</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Trees and shrubs planted 20 or 30 years ago are often overgrown, crowding walkways and blocking views. We selectively prune or remove what is past its prime and fill in with fresh plantings.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Aging Irrigation Systems</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Many Las Alturas drip and sprinkler systems are original to the home. Brittle poly pipe, broken emitters, and no smart controller means wasted water. We replace full systems and add Wi-Fi controllers.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Retaining Wall Repair</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Older block and concrete retaining walls crack and lean after years of freeze-thaw and monsoon pressure. We tear out failing walls and rebuild with proper drainage and reinforcement.</p></li></ul><a class="cs-quote-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><picture class="cs-bg-leaves"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"></picture><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was professional, punctual, and courteous. They helped me select the the right materials and offered additional design ideas. The quality of work was EXCELLENT. I highly recommend David's team to all homeowners in Las Cruces looking for reliable landscaping company. The picture below is of my backyard 1 year later and there is still no weeds! I can't think Braindard's Greenscapes enough.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Matthew Lee</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-projects-630"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Case Studies</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Alturas Project Showcase</h2></div><ul class="cs-project-group"><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><img alt="Full xeriscape and stone border renovation in Las Alturas, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-54.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Whole-Yard Renovation</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Removed overgrown shrubs, replaced 25-year-old irrigation, and installed fresh xeriscape beds on a half-acre Las Alturas lot.</p></li><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><img alt="Stone bed border and retaining wall rebuild in Las Alturas" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-16.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Retaining Wall Rebuild</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Tore out a leaning block wall and rebuilt with reinforced masonry, proper drainage, and new plantings along the base.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Alturas Landscaping FAQ</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do you update mature landscaping without starting over?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>We start with a walk-through to decide what stays and what goes. Healthy shade trees usually stay. Overgrown or dying shrubs get removed. Then we fill in with fresh native plants, new gravel or mulch, and updated irrigation. The result looks new without losing years of growth.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What does it cost to replace an old irrigation system?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>A full drip system replacement on a typical Las Alturas lot (6,000 to 10,000 sq ft of landscaped area) runs $2,500 to $6,000. That includes new poly line, emitters, valves, and a smart Wi-Fi controller. We give free on-site estimates with exact pricing.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Can you remove and replace old retaining walls?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We demo the old wall, regrade the slope, add drainage behind the new wall, and rebuild with reinforced block or stone. Walls over four feet require a city permit, and we handle that paperwork for you.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What are the best shade trees for Las Alturas?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Desert Willow, Chitalpa, and Chinese Pistache do well on the mesa. They handle alkaline soil, need moderate water, and give good canopy cover. We avoid high-water species like cottonwood unless the lot has room and the owner wants to irrigate heavily.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How often should established landscapes be pruned?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Most desert trees need pruning once or twice a year, typically late winter and after monsoon season. Shrubs like Texas Sage and Creosote can go longer between cuts. We offer maintenance plans that keep mature landscapes tidy without over-pruning.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-stats-640"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-heading-col"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Our Coverage Area</span><h2 class="cs-title">Where We Work in Las Alturas</h2></div><div class="cs-copy-col"><p class="cs-text">On the map below: the Las Alturas residential area east of Las Cruces, from Lohman Ave south to the mesa ridge, along Roadrunner Parkway and Del Rey Blvd.</p><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></div><div class="cs-map" aria-label="Map of Las Alturas, NM service area"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="430" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Las+Alturas+NM&amp;z=14&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Las Alturas, NM service area" width="1280"></iframe></div><ul class="cs-stats"><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">150+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Las Alturas Projects</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">19+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Years in the Valley</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">5/5</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Average Rating</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">100%</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Quality Guarantee</span></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-neighbors-660"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Nearby</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighboring Areas We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We also handle landscape projects in nearby Mesilla Valley communities just minutes away.</p></div><ul class="cs-neighbors"><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Las Cruces, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/sonoma-ranch-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Sonoma Ranch, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/picacho-hills-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Picacho Hills, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/east-mesa-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in East Mesa, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Las Alturas Landscape</h2><a class="cs-talk-button" href="/contact/">Get a Free Estimate</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
